---
description: Keep Digital Academic Marketplace dev servers running after edits
globs:
  - "**/*"
---

After **any** code change in this repo, ensure the site still runs:

1. From `digital-academic-marketplace/`, run **`npm run dev:restart`** in the **background** when you finish a batch of edits (unless the user asked not to touch processes). `scripts/restart-dev.sh` stops **all** matching `concurrently` / `tsx watch` / `next dev` for this monorepo (not just port listeners — `tsx watch` respawns and can cause `EADDRINUSE` if only ports are killed).
2. **`dev:restart`** = kill script + `npm run dev` (includes `predev` → rebuild `@dam/shared`).
3. If hot reload is clearly enough (tiny web-only tweak) you may skip restart — but on **`EADDRINUSE`**, API **`404`** for new routes, or odd **`500`** from Next, always run **`dev:restart`**.
4. Do **not** only tell the user to restart — run **`npm run dev:restart`** yourself when appropriate.
